"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Classic findings of chronic eosinophilic pneumonia (CEP) as seen on a&nbsp;conventional chest radiograph. The findings include bilateral, upper lobe predominant, and&nbsp;peripheral consolidative and ground-glass opacities. In CEP, lung involvement is bilateral in&nbsp;75 percent and confined to the upper lobe in&nbsp;50 percent. While these findings are \"classic\", it should be recognized that the chest imaging findings in most cases of CEP are not classic.",
